and since 2011 internationally as the International Day of Human Space Flight.

The 2004 Yuri's Night event in Los Angeles was attended by space-related figures including author Ray Bradbury, Space tourism|space tourist Dennis Tito, Ansari X Prize|X-Prize founder Peter Diamandis, *NSYNC's Lance Bass and Nichelle Nichols (Uhura from the original ''Star Trek'' series). The event included a large party with 2 dance floors and world-class DJs.<ref name=collectspace>[http://www.collectspace.com/ubb/Forum23/HTML/001097.html "Sci-Fi Legend Ray Bradbury, Mars Rover Team, Young Professionals Celebrate Spaceflight Milestone In Style At Annual Gala"]</ref>

The 2007 event in the San Francisco Bay Area was held at NASA Ames Research Center at Moffett Field in Mountain View, CA. The event featured artistic installations, technology demonstrations, and DJ music continuing through dawn of the following day.<ref name=laughingsquid>cite news |title=Photos of Yuri’s Night Bay Area 2007, A Giant Party at NASA |first=Scott |last=Beale|url=http://laughingsquid.com/photos-of-yuris-night-bay-area-2007-a-giant-party-at-nasa/ |newspaper=Laughing Squid |date=2007-04-14 |accessdate=2014-02-09</ref>

April 2011 marked the 50th anniversary of Gagarin's historic first flight.<ref name=wired20110214>
cite news |title=Celebrate 50 Years of Human Space Flight on Yuri’s Night |first=Jason Cranford |last=Teague|url=https://www.wired.com/geekdad/2011/02/celebrate-50-years-of-human-space-flight-on-yuris-night/ |newspaper=Wired |date=2011-02-14 |accessdate=2011-04-04</ref> Over 100,000 people attended 567 Yuri's Night parties in 75 countries,<ref name=aboutyn>[https://yurisnight.net/about/ About Yuri's Night]</ref> and the crew of Expedition 27 recorded a Yuri's Night celebratory greeting from the International Space Station.<ref name=ynISS>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H6BThA641Rg Yuri's Night 2011 International Space Station Crew: 50th Anniversary of Human Spaceflight (YouTube)]</ref>

Yuri's Night today

Yuri's Night events "combine space-themed partying with education and outreach". Parties and events are held at List of NASA Visitor Centers|NASA centers, museums, planetariums, schools, bars, nightclubs, houses, and other locations.<ref name=aboutyn /> Often, guests are encouraged to dress up in various space-themed attire to add to the ambiance of the show. Space-themed art, sculptures and guests are often showcased at the events. Event sizes range from small to large and often attract large crowds with headlining musical acts such as Les Claypool, N.E.R.D|N*E*R*D, Common (rapper)|Common<ref>Cite web|url=http://www.yurisnightbayarea.space/|title=Yuri's Night Bay Area|website=Yuri's Night Bay Area|access-date=2019-01-30</ref>, N.A.S.A. (musical group)|N.A.S.A., and The Crystal Method.<ref>Cite web|url=https://www.eventbrite.com/e/54418233401?aff=efbneb|title=Yuri's Night 2019 featuring The Crystal Method at The Bluebird|website=Eventbrite|language=en-us|access-date=2019-01-30</ref>

Yuri's Night has been celebrated in locations including Reno, Nevada|Reno<ref>Cite web|url=https://www.rgj.com/story/life/2018/04/08/54-photos-hipster-space-party-2018/497525002/|title=54 photos: Hipsters ... in space! Yuri's Night 2018 in Reno|website=Reno Gazette Journal|language=en|access-date=2019-01-30</ref>, Ottawa<ref>Cite web|url=https://apt613.ca/yuris-night/|title=Yuri’s Night at the Canada Aviation and Space Museum—04.13.18 – Apt613|website=apt613.ca|access-date=2019-01-30</ref><ref>Cite web|url=https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/44234876707?aff=efbneb|title=YURI'S NIGHT|website=Eventbrite|language=en-ca|access-date=2019-01-30</ref>, Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles [http://www.nbclosangeles.com/the-scene/events/Yuris-Night-119724669.html], the San Francisco Bay Area [https://www.flickr.com/photos/cameravox/sets/72157604516260066/], Huntsville, Alabama [https://web.archive.org/web/20130227025727/http://www.yurisnighthsv.org/yuri.shtml], New Orleans [https://web.archive.org/web/20130525135725/http://live.yurisnight.net/yuriss-night-new-orleans-louisiana], Inverness [https://web.archive.org/web/20130525134537/http://live.yurisnight.net/20-pictures-for-you-from-yuris-event-in-inver], Stockholm, Tel Aviv, Tokyo, Lisbon [http://www.esa.int/esaMI/Gagarin/SEMPIB6UPLG_0.html], Helsinki [http://meridiaani.org/index.php/yuri-s-night] Afghanistan, Latvia [https://web.archive.org/web/20130525135904/http://live.yurisnight.net/hi-from-latvia], Romania, Peru, Antarctica, and the International Space Station [https://web.archive.org/web/20120413052043/http://cosmiclog.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2012/04/03/11007876-feeling-down-about-spaceflight-lift-your-spirits-with-yuris-night], in addition to many other locations and virtual online celebrations [http://yurisnight.net/partylist/].

Yuri's Night is organized on a global level by an all-volunteer "Executive Team",<ref name=globalteam>[https://yurisnight.net/about/thehumans/ Yuri's Night Executive Team]</ref> which provides logistical and promotional support to Yuri's Night events worldwide. Individual organizers are responsible for registering and running their local events.<ref>Cite web|url=https://yurisnight.net/about/|title=About Yuri's Night|website=Yuri's Night|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-30</ref>

